useful in the extreme . a wonderful , lucid , entertaining and informative guide . craig takes the reader step-by-step through some of the principal works of ancient and modern philosophy , and provides us with an essential guide to the somewhat daunting task of deciphering and understanding a range of compelling thinkers and their works . with an engaging , friendly writing style ( and an excellent bibliography to encourage us to continue our journey ) , this is an indispensable little volume